Playwright Assignment: E-Commerce Shopping Cart Test
 
1. Overview
In this assignment, interns will use Playwright to automate a test scenario on an e-commerce website (e.g., Trendyol, Hepsiburada, or Amazon). The goal is to simulate a user’s shopping experience, including category navigation, product filtering, adding items to the cart, and verifying cart functionality. This assignment will help interns improve their skills in web automation and validation.
2. Objective
Navigate to an e-commerce website and select a main category (e.g., Electronics).
Randomly choose a subcategory and filter products by price range (10,000 TL - 15,000 TL).
Add a product to the cart and verify its addition, price consistency, and cart behavior.
Test advanced cart functionalities like quantity adjustments, coupon application, and item removal.
3. Requirements
3.1 Technical Requirements
Tools: Node.js, Playwright, npm.
Language: JavaScript.
Target Platform: Any e-commerce website (e.g., Trendyol recommended for Turkish market).
Output: Each step must log relevant information to the console (e.g., using console.log).
3.2 Functional Requirements
Website Navigation: Go to an e-commerce site and select a main category (e.g., "Electronics").
Subcategory Selection: Randomly select a subcategory from the chosen main category and navigate to it.
Price Filtering: Filter products in the subcategory to show items priced between 10,000 TL and 15,000 TL.
Add to Cart: Add the first product from the filtered list to the cart.
Cart Verification:
Confirm the product was added to the cart.
Compare the product’s price on the product page with the price in the cart.
Verify the product name in the cart matches the added product.
Shipping Cost Check: Check if there is a shipping fee in the cart.
Cart Quantity Check:
Record the number of items in the cart before and after adding the product.
Test the "+" and "-" buttons to adjust quantity and verify they work correctly.
Multiple Items: Add a second product and verify the total price calculation for two items.
Coupon Functionality: Test the "Add Coupon" button with an invalid coupon code and report the result.
Item Removal: Test the "Remove Item" button to ensure it deletes the product from the cart.
Suggested Additional Feature: Measure and report the page load time for the cart page.